page.title: 14Woodlands
page.content: There are small woods to the north, south and south east of the village of Denby.{Swift Wood}to the south of the village comprises of relict woodland and man-made deciduous trees. Part of the wood was part-felled in 1917 to provide wood for the war effort and has now completely grown over again. {The Wilderness}at Gunthwaithe was originally a man-made parkland for the hall and is now a woodland of deciduous trees. The wood at { {Gunthwaite Park}following the Clough Dike stream is relict. Many{footpaths}cross the area of grassland and woods providing {excellent walks}in beautiful countryside.
